up.<br><br>I am not a necromancer. Yes, I know I am a gnome in a sort of dirt-brown robe, but that's my lovely raw silk, not the Bertoxx guild uniform. I don't usually have a pet tagging along in Faydark since I just don't need one (and malachite ain't free), although I am sure seeing an elemental instead of a skeleton would make things much more obvious. So please quit giving me those slightly horrified looks when I come up. Really, I am not contagious.<br><br>I am a mage. I summon things. I like to hand them out. They are free. Really. I don't want to take your hard-earned bat wings and royal jellies and pelts and such when I try to give you things. They are simple magical trifles to share, not goods for sale.<br><br>So, if you are going about your elfy business and I come up and randomly hand you a necklace, an earring, a mantle, some bandages, a weapon, or whatever - please accept it in the spirit it was given. I am not trying to frustrate the heck out of you when I keep turning down your return offers... is there some simple way that I am just unaware of to let people know that something is a gift? The smile and wave routine just doesn't seem to be working well.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ellywig</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Capable summoner, frightfully bad linguist, and far less evil than she appears... really. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A> at: 4/5/02 8:09:24 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeneant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 470<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/5/02 8:19:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1693.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To All the